{"word":"κῆρ","slug":"κῆρ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κῆρ</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:contracted, contraction'>contr.</a> from <el>κέαρ</el>, as <el>ἦρ</el> from <el>ἔαρ</el>\n<p/><i>the heart</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>cor</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <el>κῆρι</el> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <i>with all the heart, heartily</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>:—in <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b> always <el>κέαρ.</el><p/>"}]}